        <abstract>
            <p>Comments on species with disjoined ranges; does not feel, despite CD’s expectations, that they tend to belong to small families.</p> 
<p>Gives the proportion of U. S. trees in which the sexes are separate [see <hi rend="italic">Natural selection</hi>, p. 62].</p> 
